snippet.textDisplay:
Beautiful. I can't help but notice the resemblance of the attire of the place to the attire of women in the area I come from (Himachal, India). It is but a testament to the fact that we are a single people who've been separated geographically by some rather unfortunate events in our shared history. My grandfather often told me about the years he'd spent in Lahore, and if possible, I'd like to visit that city of fables and magic sometime. It moves me that we consider ourselves to be so different from each other, being on different sides of an international border, when we have thousands of years of shared culture and tradition. 
ہند سے پيار
